<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="eyebrow reveal" data-reveal>Services</p>
    <h1 class="display display--sm reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 40ms">Loan programs tailored to your situation</h1>
    <p class="lead muted reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 80ms">
      From first-time purchases to portfolio refinances, we align program selection with how you bank, how long you plan to keep the home, and how you want your monthly cash flow to behave.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--tight">
  <div class="container service-grid">
    <article class="service-card card reveal" data-reveal>
      <figure class="media-frame service-card-media">
        <img
          src="<%= images.servicePurchase %>"
          alt="Contemporary home — purchase financing and pre-approval context"
          width="1100"
          height="619"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </figure>
      <h2 class="h3">Purchase financing</h2>
      <p class="muted">Conventional, government-backed, and jumbo paths — with a focus on appraisal timelines, seller concessions, and how your down payment affects pricing tiers.</p>
      <ul class="checklist checklist--compact">
        <li>Pre-approval letters aligned to your offer strategy.</li>
        <li>Debt-to-income planning before you fall in love with a listing.</li>
        <li>Coordination notes for your agent on financing contingencies.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="service-card card reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 60ms">
      <figure class="media-frame service-card-media">
        <img
          src="<%= images.serviceRefi %>"
          alt="Living room interior — refinancing and home equity decisions"
          width="1100"
          height="619"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </figure>
      <h2 class="h3">Refinancing</h2>
      <p class="muted">Rate-and-term, cash-out, and consolidation — modeled against break-even math so you can decide with numbers, not headlines.</p>
      <ul class="checklist checklist--compact">
        <li>Net benefit summaries including closing costs and prepaid items.</li>
        <li>ARM vs. fixed comparisons when your holding period is uncertain.</li>
        <li>Appraisal waivers and value challenges explained upfront.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
    <article class="service-card card reveal" data-reveal style="--delay: 120ms">
      <figure class="media-frame service-card-media">
        <img
          src="<%= images.serviceComplex %>"
          alt="Laptop and analytics on a desk — complex income and business documentation"
          width="1100"
          height="619"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
        />
      </figure>
      <h2 class="h3">Self-employed &amp; complex income</h2>
      <p class="muted">P&amp;L, bank-statement programs, and rental income documentation — structured so underwriters see a coherent story, not a folder of PDFs.</p>
      <ul class="checklist checklist--compact">
        <li>Entity income separation where applicable.</li>
        <li>Year-over-year trend lines lenders expect to see.</li>
        <li>Reserve requirements communicated early.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--dark">
  <div class="container narrow prose-block reveal" data-reveal>
    <h2 class="section-title">What “full service” means here</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      We do not disappear after the application. You receive milestone updates, plain-language explanations of conditions, and direct answers when something in your file needs attention. Our role is to keep the mortgage leg of your transaction as predictable as the inspection and title legs.
    </p>
    <p class="muted">
      <a class="text-link text-link--on-dark" href="/contact">Discuss your scenario with our team →</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
